    {
      "id": "3eae54e1_fe1d6cee",
      "file_path": "src/main/java/org/onap/cps/temporal/controller/rest/QueryResponseFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 117,
      "message": "I've notice an issue with generated link whose timezone offset is positive. I'm not sure exactly where it is coming from.\n\nLet's say we have the following request:\n\n  curl -X GET 'http://localhost:8082/cps-temporal/api/v1/dataspaces/bsa-dataspace-1/anchors/bsa-anchor-1/history?observedTimestampAfter=2021-08-01T00:00:00.000-0000&pageNumber=0&pageLimit=1'\n\nThen, generated next records link is: \n\n  /cps-temporal/api/v1/dataspaces/bsa-dataspace-1/anchors/bsa-anchor-1/history?observedTimestampAfter=2021-08-01T00:00:00.000+0000&pointInTime=2021-08-17T15:54:46.818-0400&pageNumber=1&pageLimit=1&sort=observed_timestamp:desc\n\nAnd requesting next records gives a Bad Request response:\n\n  {\n      \"status\": \"400\",\n      \"message\": \"observedTimestampAfter must be in 'yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSSZ' format\",\n      \"details\": null\n  }\n\nI think that \"+\" in the timestamp from the generated uri needs to be encoded with \"%2B\".",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2021-08-17 20:47:25.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
